---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Sasih (Lunar Month) - Balinese Calendar" description="Understanding the Balinese lunar months">
	<h1 class="font-display text-4xl gold-accent mb-8">Sasih (Lunar Month)</h1>

	<p class="text-lg mb-6">
		Sasih refers to the lunar months in the Balinese Saka calendar. The calendar year consists of 12 lunar months, each approximately 29-30 days long.
	</p>

	<h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-balinese-gold mt-12 mb-6">The 12 Sasih</h2>

	<ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 mb-8">
		<li><strong>Kasa</strong> - First month</li>
		<li><strong>Karo</strong> - Second month</li>
		<li><strong>Katiga</strong> - Third month</li>
		<li><strong>Kapat</strong> - Fourth month</li>
		<li><strong>Kalima</strong> - Fifth month</li>
		<li><strong>Kanem</strong> - Sixth month</li>
		<li><strong>Kapitu</strong> - Seventh month</li>
		<li><strong>Kaulu</strong> - Eighth month</li>
		<li><strong>Kasanga</strong> - Ninth month</li>
		<li><strong>Kadasa</strong> - Tenth month</li>
		<li><strong>Jestha</strong> - Eleventh month</li>
		<li><strong>Sadha</strong> - Twelfth month</li>
	</ol>

	<h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-balinese-gold mt-12 mb-6">Lunar Year Structure</h2>

	<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-8">
		<li><strong>Year length</strong>: 354 or 355 days</li>
		<li><strong>Month length</strong>: 29 or 30 days</li>
		<li><strong>New Year (Nyepi)</strong>: Usually falls in March</li>
		<li><strong>Epoch</strong>: Started in 78 CE</li>
	</ul>

	<h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-balinese-gold mt-12 mb-6">Nampih (Intercalary Month)</h2>

	<p class="mb-6">
		To keep the lunar calendar aligned with the solar year, an intercalary month called Nampih is occasionally added. This happens approximately every 3 years.
	</p>

	<div class="code-block mb-6">
		<pre><code class="language-rust">use balinese_calendar::BalineseDate;

let date = BalineseDate::from_ymd(2023, 1, 1)?;

// Check if this is a Nampih month
if date.is_nampih() {
    println!("This is a Nampih (intercalary) month");
}</code></pre>
	</div>

	<h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-balinese-gold mt-12 mb-6">Moon Phases</h2>

	<p class="mb-6">
		The Balinese calendar also tracks moon phases:
	</p>

	<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-8">
		<li><strong>Purnama</strong> - Full moon (15th day of month)</li>
		<li><strong>Tilem</strong> - New moon (last day of month)</li>
	</ul>

	<div class="code-block mb-6">
		<pre><code class="language-rust">let date = BalineseDate::from_ymd(2023, 1, 1)?;

if date.is_purnama() {
    println!("Today is Purnama (full moon)");
}

if date.is_tilem() {
    println!("Today is Tilem (new moon)");
}</code></pre>
	</div>

	<h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-balinese-gold mt-12 mb-6">Working with Sasih in Code</h2>

	<div class="code-block mb-6">
		<pre><code class="language-rust">use balinese_calendar::BalineseDate;

let date = BalineseDate::from_ymd(2023, 1, 1)?;

// Get the Sasih (lunar month)
println!("Sasih: {}", date.sasih_name());

// Get the Saka year
println!("Saka Year: {}", date.saka_year());

// Get the day within the month
println!("Day in month: {}", date.sasih_day());</code></pre>
	</div>

